text.tspan: The events shown here are the events that occur in the space of single video cycle. This is an interpretation
of the Atari 2600 as seen in the emulator, Gopher2600.
The order of these events are important. The dashed vertical lines indicate the major time slices.
Events above the thick Video Tick arrow occur every video cycle without fail, while events below the line
occur only every third video clock, just before the next CPU cycle.
Events in the shaded areas are delayed events. The yellow area are delayed events governed at the level of
the entire TIA package while the purple area are governed at the sprite level. Each sprite governs its own
delays (related to when the sprite ticks).
